What are you trying to say here?  You have apparently missed the point.  Freedom of speech and freedom from the consequences of what you say are two different things.  Also, you can't be thrown in jail for having an opinion.  But, you can be thrown in jail for acting on your opinion.Try to be more descriptive with your argument.  You may have a valid point, but it's not clear in what you are writing.